      • parseJson

        public static Value parseJson​(@NotNull
                              @NotNull ScimResource res,
                              Attribute attr,
                              com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode fnode,
                              IBulkIdResolver bulkIdResolver)
                       throws SchemaException,
                              java.text.ParseException
        Static method used to parse a JsonNode object for its appropriate SCIM Value type based on the declared Attribute.
        Parameters:
        res - The id of the scim resource being mapped (if available or null)
        attr - The SCIM Attribute type for the value being parsed
        fnode - A JsonNode representing the attribute/value node.
        bulkIdResolver - This resolver is used for bulk operations where an Identifier may be temporary.
        Returns:
        The parsed Value instance. See com.independentid.scim.resource package for sub-classes (Complex, String, Boolean, DateTime, Binary, Reference).
        Throws:
        SchemaException - May be thrown by ValueUtil parser.
        java.text.ParseException - May be thrown by ValueUtil parser.

      • parseValueType

        public static java.lang.String parseValueType​(java.lang.String name,
                                              java.lang.String value)
        Takes an attribute name and value and attempts to detect the data type specified in the value. This is used when a SCIM filter is specified with attribute name not defined in the configured schema. While not declared in the SCIM schema, the attribute may still be valid within the backend provider. Will not detect BINARY (base64 encoded) data.
        Parameters:
        name - A String containing the name of the attribute (e.g. "id")
        value - A String (e.g. from a URL filter) containing a data value
        Returns:
        Returns the SCIM Value type constant (e.g. Attribute.TYPE_String) detected.

      • isReturnable

        public static boolean isReturnable​(java.lang.String name,
                                   RequestCtx ctx)
        This checks to see if an attribute name is returnable. This is a *last resort* method as it searches the configuration to locate a match. Where possible use the variant of this method that includews Schema.
        Parameters:
        name - A String containing the name of the attribute to be checked. Can be a short id, partial path (e.g. User) or full path with schema id.
        ctx - The request context that specifies included/excluded attributes
        Returns:
        true if the attribute is returnable.

      • isReturnable

        public static boolean isReturnable​(ExtensionValues ext,
                                   RequestCtx ctx)
        This method checks to see if any of an extensions values are returnable in the current request context.
        Parameters:
        ext - An ExtensionValues object containing the set of Values for a particular extension.
        ctx - The RequestCtx containing the returned and excluded attributes params.
        Returns:
        true if the provided ExtensionValues object has at least 1 returnable value.
